reviews.text: The national museum has been closed since 2016 and projected opening date still hasn't been released to us the public. They're also currently not using the art gallery space on the museum grounds for art but rather to display posters with information on various things. Very boring and uninformative. Zero creativity. The museum  that was the same for years was better than this make-shift museum of posters. Definitely not a place to take guests or children. Disappointing.
I really like the art gallery.
Nice exhibition currently on. Expected more though and amenities like toilets definitely need an update and better maintenance. Loads of potential
It was a great experience going there,, I got the chance to be explained to about all the different kinds of things that are in the museum
Free and very informative. Needs to finish the renovations soon.
This is a historical place to learn about how Botswana got their independence from Britain. There you will find three statutes of grey men who went to england to get independence for Batswana.
Just made a u turn next to them but they looked sturdy and weatherproof.
The guide is great. The viewing is perfect. Always opened
A good historical place with a rich history dating back to the1800
The history of knowing where botswana came from excellent tour guide who knew everything he was doing

Very quiet and clean. Also very luscious green grass that makes it very nice for a picnic or just to go read there while surrounded by nature. Would definitely go back again. However,their tourist shop needs a bit of attention and doesn't really have much variety.
A well manicured, scenic and spacious garden. It's peaceful and there are many private spots of you're looking for some privacy or just some alone time with beautiful views. I love it.

The gardens look amazing. There are boards available everywhere with additional information on trees and plants. There is also a fabulous trail that goes up alongside the hill, with beautiful views of the area.
More than enough space to picnic. It's a shame that the jungle gym has been removed.

The gardens are beautiful and the grass is green. I like the coffee that the restuarant makes. The hiking trail is nice, and it feels like you're going on an adventure when you take it. 

I would really recommend anyone to go there. 

But, i took my girlfriend to the gardens today, on a picnic, and one of the men working there took pictures of us. It was weird.
Very nice relaxing. Ideal for picnic for a romantic picnic or just a outing for the family. Trails and braai also ideal

There is a subway station right at the stadium. Very convenient. 

There are several things to do there... stadium tour, 3D museum, etc. The admission fee is not too expensive. 

The structure is just impressive.

Very beautiful architecture, one of the most aesthetically pleasing stadiums in the world. Across from it is the National Aquatics center where Michael Phelps an Olympic record 8 gold medals during the 2008 Olympics in Beijing. It's a lot nicer at night.

The national stadium has a very impressive architecture and was held the Summer Olympic Games in 2008 - it’ll be also the host for the Winter Olympic Games in 2022. 

Please be advised to go thru the checkpoints “without” buying a ticket cuz the ticket for the so called “birds nest” is in front of the National stadium and costs u 80 Yuan.
Very attractive and good design ... after event the stadium still usefull and still many people also tourists visit here
It was a great place to go and see, there's a museum and places to eat, wort a look at the birds nest
Lovely restaurant, very eco friendly. The food is nice. The atmosphere is nice and relaxed, good for hanging out with friends
Best coffee and cake spot in the country, with a nice view of the city and the sunset. The ambiance here is exactly what you need to set the time of any day.

Beautiful nursery and restaurant with incredible trees! A huge variety of plants available for purchase, as well as ornaments, pots etc. And a good restaurant with friendly staff. It can be a bit chilly in the shade so take something warm with just in case. Fun play area for the kids. Had freshly squeezed naartjie juice made with the nurseries own naartjies, which was a great treat.
Good food, good ambience....... i only worry that their speedpoint payment takes long to process card payments and it has been for a couple of days. Otherwise it is a good place to enjoy lunch.
Great atmosphere. Open space and indoor sitting available to choose from. Well prepared food. And in weekends, music by dj
This place is a breeze of fresh air..
